import {Navbar, Nav, Image, Container} from 'react-bootstrap'
import './App.css';
import logo from "./Assets/Logo.png"

function App() {
  return (
    <>
    <Navbar collapseOnSelect variant='dark' bg='dark' expand='md'>
      <Navbar.Brand className='twitter'>
        
      </Navbar.Brand>
      <Navbar.Toggle aria-controls='responsive-navbar-nav' />
      <Navbar.Collapse id='responsive-navbar-nav'>
        <Nav>
          <Nav.Link href='/'>Home</Nav.Link>
          <Nav.Link href='search'>Search Twitter</Nav.Link>
          <Nav.Link href='random'>Random Twitter</Nav.Link>
        </Nav>
      </Navbar.Collapse>
    </Navbar>
    
    {/* <Navbar activeKey="/home" class='container' expand='lg' fixed='top'>
    
      <Navbar.Brand class='img-fluid' className='nav-logo'>
      <Image fluid src={logo}/> 
      </Navbar.Brand>
      <Nav className='justify-content-right'>
      
        <Nav.Link href="#contact" className='contactLink align-baseline' >
         contact
        </Nav.Link>
       
     
      </Nav>
     
    </Navbar> */}
    
    
    </>
  );
}

export default App;
